“Hello, Red Riding Hood! Come in! I’m making bread for dinner.”  

Red stepped inside, and they chatted for a while. Then she asked, “Where are your brothers?”  

The first pig laughed. “My brothers built houses too, but they’re strong—made of bricks. I built mine of straw, but it’s cozy enough.”  

Just then, the second little pig walked in, carrying a bag of flour. He greeted Red warmly, and they shared a laugh.  

Later, Red went to visit the third little pig’s house, which was even bigger and sturdier. The third pig was working on a new chair for his living room.  

“Hey, Red! Want to stay for dinner?” he asked.  

