That night, when Red arrived at grandma’s house, she told her all about the pigs. Grandma smiled and said, “It’s nice to see the pigs making friends. They’re not just builders—they’re kind hearts too.”  

And from that day on, whenever Red visited the forest, she would stop by the pigs’ houses, and they would have tea together.  

And they all lived happily ever after.

